n de calcio en las arterias\\Ncoronarias ≥300 o en un percentil ≥75","guid":"TbrZFg4SB-LsRr2O_aFDQA","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"29","text":"índice tobillo-brazo <0,90","guid":"FHOVHcjsKihiAZ6KBR3WWA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"0","text":"Grupos de riesgo\\Nespecíficos","guid":"aPjOH7bt4sU0M11LfVVHDw","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"Mujeres","guid":"C5Sn_tut3SeOL9--KdfpdA","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"Hipertensión arterial","guid":"_8AKvvhjfIy8l7TqdeLoWA","children":[{"id":"36","parent":"35","text":"hipertensión arterial es la causa\\Nprincipal de muerte en las mujeres","guid":"Vowg5-J5cxLnb55_rmyvVg","children":[]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"34","text":"ECV continúa siendo la causa principal de muerte en las mujeres","guid":"gWRXscy1gTcW7LD7g_bkvw","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"34","text":"hiperlipemia, la diabetes tipo 2, la obesidad y el tabaquismo confieren un\\Nmayor riesgo de enfermedad coronaria en las mujeres que en los varones","guid":"3Gsp6QFi3o6wyUi7SzPFKQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"33","text":"Obesidad y síndrome\\Nmetabólico","guid":"gKfVenRiUq-eTeDOlpV6pg","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"glucemia elevada, obesidad central, bajo nivel de colesterol-HDL,\\Nniveles elevados de triglicéridos y presión arterial elevada.","guid":"Y4HKHvvFadIlnGnyuqHRlA","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"33","text":"\\\\*Diabetes \\\\*\\\\/mellitus\\\\/","guid":"8zWiPFhN50uD7r6FQL0LbA","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"equivalente del riesgo de ECV\\Nriesgo de enfermedad cardiovascular es 2-4 veces mayor","guid":"f-m_CvvlMG02Ke9opqjMXg","children":[]}]},{"id":"43","parent":"33","text":"Trastornos inflamatorios\\Nsistémicos","guid":"fuRZY7smEjNsEu1uY9w69g","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"artritis reumatoide","guid":"5ne_Ml6tFClc_WHI67dEvQ","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"En los pacientes con artritis reumatoide, el riesgo de enfermedad coronaria\\Naumenta 1,5 a 2 veces en comparación con la población en general.","guid":"jq_FK_5wmzhMnLhOYGA6-w","children":[]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"43","text":"lupus eritematoso sistémico.","guid":"n1iJB1fZIp-bwy4dpOIhGg","children":[]}]},{"id":"47","parent":"33","text":"Enfermedad\\Nrenal crónica","guid":"u3Ltp35x0s6tlJ-63G5kLA","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"riesgo de muerte relacionada con ECV es 5-30 veces\\Nmayor en los pacientes sometidos a diálisi","guid":"Xq3S5w7knkqsu7xFesDlog","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"47","text":"no se benefician de la prevención secundaria con estatinas","guid":"TAfgQxyu832ZZr8HDqF5VQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"50","parent":"33","text":"VIH","guid":"mH0pih3WXTLCzmZA_xEjiQ","children":[{"id":"51","parent":"50","text":"aumenta 1,5-2 veces el riesgo de enfermedad coronaria.","guid":"FzWUuAI3kZ9_xLws0xosAw","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":51,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Cardiología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/MKSAP - 18/Cardiología","filename":"1. Factores de riesgo de enfermedad cardiovascular","id":"map_1191","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"1. Factores de riesgo de enfermedad cardiovascular"}